<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/05e4419a6ea5958c3772638445120096.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 3 and A = 65 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>1.4</li><li>3.3</li><li>25.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({65}\right)}}}=\frac{{3}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{3}}{{\tan{{\left({65}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{1.398922974465}\approx{1.4}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={3}^{{2}}+{1.398922974465}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}+{1.956985488486}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={10.956985488486}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{10.956985488486}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{3.3101337568875}\approx{3.3}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{65}^{\circ}\approx{25}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

